The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, March 10 (PTI): Thirteen hundred cases are pending against sitting MPs and MLAs in various courts, law and justice minister H.R. Bhardwaj said in the Rajya Sabha today, quoting figures from a parliamentary standing committee report.          
	The CBI is reportedly investigating around 65 such cases. The parliamentary panel on personnel, public grievances and law and justice, while doing a study on electoral reforms, learnt of the cases against the sitting MPs and MLAs.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): The government is planning to bring in a special marriage act for Sikhs in response to a long-standing demand from the community. This was stated by law and justice minister H.R. Bhardwaj in the Rajya Sabha on Monday.                   
	Toronto (PTI): The plush Canada mansion of Amit Kumar, the alleged mastermind of the multi-crore kidney transplant racket, has been put up for sale after his wife and children vacated it two weeks ago. Kumar had bought the house, located in Brampton, for $610,000.                  
	Dubai (PTI): A Dubai-based Indian school has requested the Central Board of Secondary Education to consider postponing the CBSE exams by an hour in the UAE from next year because heavy traffic made it difficult for students to reach the test venues on time.                  
	Srinagar (PTI): Troops of the 22 Rashtriya Rifles in Jammu and Kashmir have arrested four suspected Jaish-e-Mohammed militants, a defence spokesman said on Monday.                                                                                                                           
